      "text": "Marcus started talking. \"So after you carry the one, you've got to regroup the hundreds column, and that means—\" He paused. Eli looked up. Marcus's forehead was scrunched. Marcus chewed the inside of his cheek. \"Wait,\" Marcus said. \"I'm not sure either.\" He said it the same way Eli had said it. Like it was just a fact. Like it wasn't the end of the world. Eli felt something strange and warm move through his chest."
    },
    {
      "pageNumber": 11,
